Pre-Game Insights: Safaa Kasraoui mentions that Guinea has not proved an easy opponent in this year's tournament, as it managed to draw its first game against Cameroon 1-1, despite playing with ten men since the end of the first half.
The Guinean team has secured its first win against Gambia 1-0, securing them 4 points and the second position in Group C standings.
Senegal have embarked on a successful journey this year so far by defeating Gambia 3-0 and five-time champion Cameroon 3-1.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Supporters watching from the sideline in Cote d'Ivoire will gather for this key meeting at the Charles Konan Banny Stadium in Yamoussoukro, while those watching remotely can follow the match on Sky Sports Main Event, Sky Sports Premier League, and Sky Sports Ultra HDR.
Senegal is aiming to win today against its Guinean counterpart in order to earn 9 points in the Group C standings.
Champions of the last AFCON edition in 2021, Senegal will seek to continue on the same track of success to achieve a third win streak.
